track.name: Rock Me
comments: Muddy, you are the one! The mudrerer of big Blues...yeah!
Mmmmm, yesssss...feel the base in his voice, the harmonica tickling my spine and this beat moving me like a puppet!
Another fine example of how "changing music" isn't "steeling music" according to Zeppelin. The song "you shook me" is a dead on rip off of this tune.

Effortless !
I'm a King Bee is a great track too by our Mr Waters, check it out then listen to the Stones version
one of those canonical blues joints; i love it!

Love Muddy Waters, love blues. Hav you tried listening to Rory Gallaher?
Some of his music was inspired with this generation of Blues.
